[h3 id=AboutTheGame 
	" About the Game
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Circus
	]em
	" is a 1984 text adventure published by Digital Fantasia and is the 6th game in Brian Howarth's 
	[em 
		"Mysterious Adventures
	]em
	" series. Your task is to sneak into the circus, blow it up and escape unharmed. It is not to be confused with another game called 
	[em 
		"Circus
	]em
	" published by Load 'n' Run in 1987. which is an action game that I will also be trying out at some point.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=AboutTheTas 
	" About the TAS
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This TAS aims to complete the game as fast as possible.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=TapeLoading 
	" Tape Loading
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The first ~88% of this TAS is simply loading the tape. Loading finishes on frame 11454 (~4:40). The loading segment is not included in the temp encode and the actual gameplay is only about 30 seconds long.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=DisablingPictures 
	" Disabling Pictures
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"For the Mysterious Adventures series, we can press enter to toggle between pictures or text description. This saves a 
	[b 
		"MASSIVE
	]b
	" amount of time due to the games not having to process all the pictures.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=TypingPatterns 
	" Typing Patterns
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The usual optimal typing pattern looks like this:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"T
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Y
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"P
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"N
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"G
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But a few times, this pattern can be disrupted by typing the 2nd letter of a command 2-3 frames after the first during text loading. Then the pattern looks like this:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"T
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Y
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"P
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"N
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"G
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It's possible to input the 1st letter of a command while a picture is loading. Depending on whether the game lags from this or not, this can save 1 frame every time it's done.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Also, we can only press one key 10 times a second, meaning that when we have to type 2 of the same letter in a row, there's a 5 frame delay.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WordShortening 
	" Word Shortening
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Words that are 5 letters or longer don't have to be typed out in full, and can instead be shortened to 4 letters, for example:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" PANEL = PANE
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" TRAPDOOR = TRAP
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" TERMINAL = TERM
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"You get the idea.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Gameplay continues like this while waiting through cutscenes until input ends on frame 12966, when we enter the command "DRIV CAR" (DRIVE CAR).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"That's all from me. Thanks for reading.
	$LF
]div
